outputs.output_descr:
The overall goal of the Project is to Contribute to better access to justice for marginalized and vulnerable persons (at least seventy per cent women)- by establishing mechanisms for dialogue between the government and civil society to address key challenges in access to justice and by enhancing the capacities of the government and civil society in advancing rule of law reforms
The project has four identified outcomes (first two outcomes are implemented by Consortium partner of the Project) that together will produce the impact:
Outcome 1: Legal awareness raising fosters legal protection of vu
